250 g Ground Beef
6 unit(s) Flour Tortillas
½ cup Cheddar Cheese, shredded
90 mL Dill Pickle, sliced
4 tbsp Mayonnaise
2 tbsp Ketchup
1 tbsp BBQ Seasoning
113 g Green Cabbage, shredded
1 tsp Dill-Garlic Spice Blend
½ tbsp White Wine Vinegar
1 unit(s) Green Onion
½ tbsp Oil*
0.06 tsp Salt*
0.13 tsp Pepper*

Thinly slice green onion.
Drain pickles.
Very finely chop 2 tbsp (4 tbsp) pickles.
Thinly slice remaining pickles.

Add ketchup, chopped pickles and 3 tbsp (6 tbsp) mayo to a small bowl. Season with pepper, then stir to combine.

Combine Dill-Garlic Spice Blend, remaining mayo and half the vinegar (use all for 4 ppl) in a large bowl.
Add cabbage and green onions. Season with salt and pepper, then toss to combine.

Heat a large non-stick pan over medium-high heat.
When hot, add 1/2 tbsp (1 tbsp) oil, then beef. Cook, breaking up beef into smaller pieces, until no pink remains, 4-5 min.**
Remove and discard excess fat, if desired.
Add BBQ Seasoning, then stir to coat.
Remove from heat and cover to keep warm.

Just before serving, wrap tortillas in paper towels.
Microwave until tortillas are warm and flexible, 30 sec-1 min. (TIP: You can skip this step if you don't want to warm the tortillas!)

Divide tortillas between plates.
Spread secret sauce onto tortillas.
Divide beef, remaining pickles, cheese and some slaw between tortillas.
Serve any remaining slaw alongside.